Key Match Events: Simon Msuva scored the opening goal for Tanzania in the 11th minute
Patson Daka scored the equalizing goal for Zambia in the 88th minute
Post-Match Reflections: Tanzania were denied a first win at the African Cup of Nations
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game was played at the Laurent Pokou Stadium in San-Pedro, Ivory Coast
Others: The result left Morocco top with four points, the Congolese and Zambians on two points and Tanzania bottom on one, after two games each
